To calculate the effective number of tests across phenotypes, we calculated the correlation matrix between the gene p values for the four osteoarthritis phenotypes, and obtained the eigenvalues of this matrix. The effective number of tests Neff for phenotypes was then calculated as \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
